  "response": "No, six hours of sleep is generally not enough for a 10-year-old. According to sleep guidelines from organizations like the American Academy of Sleep Medicine (AASM) and the National Sleep Foundation, children aged 6 to 12 years old typically need **9 to 12 hours of sleep per night** for optimal health, development, and functioning. \n\nGetting only six hours of sleep could lead to issues such as difficulty concentrating, moodiness, weakened immune function, and impaired academic performance. To support their growth and well-being, it\u2019s important to ensure they get adequate sleep by establishing a consistent bedtime routine and creating a sleep-friendly environment.",
